  "texts": [
    "This may be due to the increasing number of user instructions as the dataset size grows, which is unnecessary for the model to learn.",
    "Overall, this indicates that π SFT should be trained with packing and loss masking, over a large collection of high-quality datasets as in Table 1.",
    "Following prior work, we use DPO (Rafailov et al., 2023) and continue training from the last iteration of SFT from Section 3.2.",
    "We selected DPO for our study because it is one of the most widely used algorithms for preference optimization (Tunstall et al., 2023b; Jiang et al., 2024; Yang et al., Yuan et al., 2024), despite the recent appearance of many alternatives (Meng et al., 2024; Gorbatovski et al., 2024; Ethayarajh et al., 2024).",
    "We then compare different training settings such as choosing sequence length/reference model; tuning beta; scaling offline alignment; and filtering preference datasets."
  ]
